{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"d7b9d7ce3dd5cac5","type":"group","x":-2480,"y":-400,"width":1700,"height":760,"label":"replay phase"},
		{"id":"57cec0e8a798e047","type":"group","x":-2480,"y":-1200,"width":1260,"height":700,"label":"capture phase"},
		{
			"id":"e64554346dbbae90",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# HTTP proxy server (MITMPROXY)",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"textAlign":"center",
				"shape":null
			},
			"x":-1560,
			"y":-240,
			"width":400,
			"height":240,
			"color":"2"
		},
		{
			"id":"0421f81b56131fed",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# AUT (web client)",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","shape":"pill"},
			"x":-1950,
			"y":-200,
			"width":340,
			"height":160
		},
		{
			"id":"c5866dbc28629440",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### - image regression testing-based oracle\n### - we compare screenshots and highlight differences in user workflows that may violate the user privileges\n### - test are generated considering altered HTTP responses",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"textAlign":null,
				"border":"invisible"
			},
			"x":-2480,
			"y":440,
			"width":1200,
			"height":280
		},
		{
			"id":"7d589e1d3b174055",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# AUT's server",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","shape":"pill"},
			"x":-1100,
			"y":-200,
			"width":300,
			"height":160
		},
		{
			"id":"2dc8ee1a27fe9c34",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Aren't automatic interactions with the GUI blocked?\n\n- Often they are. Commercial web applications may detect browser automation by checking signals such as `navigator.webdriver` and many other browser or behavioral fingerprints exposed by automation frameworks.\n\n- Instead of launching its own browser, ==Playwright can connect to an existing Chrome instance through the Chrome DevTools Protocol (CDP)==. In this case, Playwright controls the browser remotely rather than creating it.\n\n- If the browser was launched as a regular user browser (rather than by an automation framework), ==some automation-specific signals, such as `navigator.webdriver`, may not be present==. While this does not eliminate all possible detection techniques, it is enough to interact automatically with most applications\n\n- CAPTCHAs and login flows can be completed manually before Playwright attaches to the existing browser session and automates the remaining interactions.",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center"},
			"x":-2770,
			"y":880,
			"width":990,
			"height":620,
			"color":"4"
		},
		{
			"id":"5a97235530738cc9",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Advantages\n\n- ==Tests realistic user workflows instead of requiring exhaustive exploration== of the entire application.\n- ==Independent== of both front-end and back-end implementation ==technologies==.\n- Can be integrated into the development lifecycle to validate newly introduced features before deployment.\n- Does not require access to the application's source code or server-side implementation (black-box testing).\n- Operates on deployed applications, making it applicable to commercial closed-source systems.\n- Detects authorization ==issues that emerge from the interaction between the GUI and the back-end,== rather than considering each layer in isolation.\n- Naturally supports Single-Page Applications (SPAs) by observing the runtime UI state.\n- Allows testers to combine manual exploration (e.g., authentication, CAPTCHAs, complex workflows) with automated security analysis.\n- Produces ==reproducible test cases== from recorded user interactions.\n- Can be applied incrementally: only modified workflows need to be revalidated after introducing a new feature.",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"border":null
			},
			"x":-1720,
			"y":880,
			"width":1120,
			"height":920,
			"color":"5"
		},
		{
			"id":"d13b15f7add9c596",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# 2. Replay phase",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":-2900,
			"y":-400,
			"width":420,
			"height":80
		},
		{
			"id":"388f78ebb3d00df9",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# 🤖",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible","textAlign":"center"},
			"x":-2460,
			"y":-160,
			"width":80,
			"height":80
		},
		{
			"id":"7814a86d03561607",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# 3. Test generation phase",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":-2900,
			"y":480,
			"width":420,
			"height":120
		},
		{
			"id":"aea435eed0b1e611",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Revise logic flow",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-500,
			"y":-40,
			"width":460,
			"height":60
		},
		{
			"id":"01485a63b49a8e25",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Motivating example\n\n- client-side flaws may lead to business losses\n- E2E test may fail to detect these flaws\n- information in the GUI can lead to authorization bypass, complementing network tampering",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-500,
			"y":120,
			"width":380,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"19f4f7261c8cd564",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Motivating example\n\n- client-side flaws may lead to business losses",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-500,
			"y":-440,
			"width":380,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"1d9c0739d3c7f8fa",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## E2E AuthZ testing approach\n- Augmented Testing approach\n- based on HTTP proxy server and capture-replay mechanisms",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"border":"invisible",
				"textAlign":null
			},
			"x":0,
			"y":120,
			"width":480,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"6b7513eb2143ee26",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Front-end centered BAC framework\n- from authorization-related CWE to OI/OP/OT",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":0,
			"y":-440,
			"width":400,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"2d3a0d91b5c95c74",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# 🤖",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible","textAlign":"center"},
			"x":-2450,
			"y":-680,
			"width":80,
			"height":80
		},
		{
			"id":"440cd800308d93d4",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"- register worflow \n(eg. home > button 1 > page 2 > ...)\n- produce screenshots after each action",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"textAlign":"center",
				"shape":null,
				"border":"invisible"
			},
			"x":-2340,
			"y":-780,
			"width":460,
			"height":200,
			"color":"2"
		},
		{
			"id":"3b56c8eea3967d6d",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Current logic flow",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-500,
			"y":-580,
			"width":460,
			"height":60
		},
		{
			"id":"9ced7a6b602fb4f6",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# to \"we propose a semi-automatic approach to generate authorization-centered E2E tests. It is validated in 44 apps and found xxx BAC\"",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","shape":"pill"},
			"x":390,
			"y":-1140,
			"width":820,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"0549d45d14e2db90",
