		},
		{
			"id":"8f200e522722a525",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# from \"we tamper with 44 apps using known techniques and we find xxx BAC\"",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","shape":"pill"},
			"x":-270,
			"y":-1140,
			"width":540,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"7bd935dbc204f359",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# 1. Capture phase",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":-2900,
			"y":-1200,
			"width":420,
			"height":80
		},
		{
			"id":"9097d78224edeb5a",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# 👤",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible","textAlign":"center"},
			"x":-2460,
			"y":-960,
			"width":100,
			"height":80
		},
		{
			"id":"25c11423136b3e28",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Applicability on Empirical study\n- 44 applications\n- 1 user workflow per application",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"border":"invisible",
				"textAlign":null
			},
			"x":560,
			"y":120,
			"width":340,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"eb37d52777f39b75",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Tampering techniques\n- JavaScript Component Hijacking\n- HTTP response tampering",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":520,
			"y":-440,
			"width":420,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"bd5e7fb304ca35cd",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Result modeled on a front-end centered BAC framework\n- OI/OP/OT are derived from the results of the study\n- and then mapped to existing CWEs",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":1000,
			"y":120,
			"width":400,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"64a3d0c663095fb8",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Empirical study\n- methodology\n- testing protocol\n- results",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":1020,
			"y":-440,
			"width":420,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"4ee8f2e29d2003d4",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Problems:\n- \"web front-ends\" is too general, we focus on SPA\n- if we study the \"role\", why didn't we focus on apps that are known to be vulnerable (from CVEs)?\n- The title must refer to features in commercial apps\n- We should highlight the novel approach",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":1880,
			"y":-300,
			"width":715,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"0147c7d8dcc8b485",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# On the Role of Web Front-Ends in Broken Access Control. Vulnerabilities: An Empirical Study",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":1880,
			"y":-580,
			"width":715,
			"height":200
		},
		{
			"id":"f5a5db7bfc190a01",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Authorization Flaws in Commercial SPA-Based Web Applications: An Empirical Study through Front-End Analysis",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":2680,
			"y":-580,
			"width":776,
			"height":160
		},
		{
			"id":"164b3b00d1bc62a8",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Authorization-Centered End-to-End Testing for Detecting Authorization Flaws in Web Applications",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":2720,
			"y":-340,
			"width":676,
			"height":160
		},
		{
			"id":"97bb4c8791c62880",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Augmented Authorization Testing: Generating End-to-End Security Tests from User Workflows",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":2720,
			"y":-140,
			"width":676,
			"height":150
		},
		{
			"id":"7fec415b12c8b6d2",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# RQ\n\nRQ1: Can authorization-centered E2E testing uncover real authorization-related vulnerabilities in modern web applications?\n- type of vulnerability /classification (eg IDOR, MFLAC,...) \n- causes (OI/OP /OT architectures) \n- case studies \n\nWe find real BAC and describe them\n\nRQ2: Can authorization-centered E2E tests be generated automatically from captured user interactions through HTTP response mutation?\n- replay success rate\n- overhead/performance \n- human effort \n- test stability \n\nWe generate test automatically \n\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2620,
			"y":2000,
			"width":840,
			"height":800
		}
	],
